---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="SnapAtlas Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for SnapAtlas and North Shore Apps."
>
  <section class="container-custom pt-14 pb-16 md:pt-20">
    <p class="section-kicker">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mt-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">Last updated: 2026-07-21</p>

    <div class="card mt-8 space-y-6 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Overview</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          SnapAtlas is developed by North Shore Apps. This policy explains what information may be processed when
          using SnapAtlas and this website.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Application data handling</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          SnapAtlas is designed to organize photo libraries on your own Windows system. Your photo files and metadata
          remain under your control on your local storage unless you explicitly export or share them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Website analytics and logs</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          This website may collect standard web telemetry such as aggregate traffic data and request logs to maintain
          service reliability and improve content.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Third-party platforms</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Download and purchase flows may involve third-party services such as Microsoft Store and GitHub, each with
          their own privacy terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          For privacy questions, contact <a href="mailto:support@northshoreapps.com" class="text-teal-800 font-semibold">support@northshoreapps.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
